    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="440" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Thayer</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 30.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 14, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of the 1st ultimo, No. 45,
                            communicating intelligence of the death of Mr. Charles March, late
                            United States vice-consul at Cairo, was duly received and has been made
                            public here, where the deceased was well and favorably known. The
                            circumstances which attended his sudden and unexpected death, with your
                            just and feeling tribute to his character and attainments, will possess
                            a melancholy interest to his friends and to the public generally.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William S. Thayer</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Alexandria.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
